prompts.primary:
Generate structured data schema markup for the following page.

## Source

- **Source File / Reference:** {{source_file}}
- **Page URL:** {{page_url}}
- **Schema Type:** {{primary_schema_type}}
- **Additional Schemas:** {{additional_schemas}}
- **Integration Target:** {{integration_framework}}

If source file is not provided, analyze the page content and details below.
If schema type is "Auto-detect from content", choose the best primary @type based on page content; still add complementary schemas (e.g. BreadcrumbList, Organization) when appropriate.

## Page Metadata

- **Title / Headline:** {{page_title}}
- **Meta Description:** {{meta_description}}
- **Author:** {{author_name}}
- **Date Published:** {{date_published}}
- **Date Modified:** {{date_modified}}
- **Organization / Brand:** {{organization_name}}
- **Logo URL:** {{logo_url}}

## Images

{{image_urls}}

## Page Content (primary analysis source — do not invent fields)

{{page_content}}

## Structured Inputs

**FAQ Q&A:**
{{faq_content}}

**HowTo Steps:**
{{howto_steps}}

**Breadcrumbs:**
{{breadcrumbs}}

**Product Details:**
{{product_info}}

---

Follow your full process:

1. Analyze page type, title, description, author, dates, images, FAQ, steps, and pricing from the inputs
2. Determine schema type(s) — use specified type or auto-detect; combine with additional schemas when relevant
3. Generate **valid JSON-LD** with required and recommended properties (omit unknown fields, never fabricate)
4. Provide **framework-specific integration code** for {{integration_framework}}
5. List **rich result eligibility** (what Google rich results this enables)
6. Include validation link: https://search.google.com/test/rich-results

If data is insufficient for a required field, note what's missing rather than fabricating values.

Produce output in the exact format from your instructions.
